ed.com/alexkantrowitz/nothing-is-going-to-happen-to-facebook-or-mark-zucker=
berg)!): it really is different this time.

The story will endure not because of animosity toward political data use bu=
t because it perfectly touches upon a deeper anxiety about our online priva=
cy that=E2=80=99s been building for years. Indeed, the Cambridge Analytica =
scandal could well be the catalyst for a much bigger targeting revolt =E2=
=80=94 a full-scale personal and public reckoning that looks at the way we=
=E2=80=99ve used the internet for the last decade. It=E2=80=99s a moment th=
at forces us, collectively, to step back and think about what we sacrificed=
 for a more convenient and connected world. And on an internet that feels i=
ncreasingly toxic it=E2=80=99s hard to look at the tradeoffs we=E2=80=99ve =
made and feel like we=E2=80=99re getting a fair deal.
